<para id="fs-id1170308297050">We must remember to check the order of the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> values within each group as well. We notice that the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> values in the second group are not in order from the least value to the greatest value; these values thus must be reordered, meaning the median <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> value for that group is 70.</para><table id="fs-id1170308482000" summary="This table holds data for 3 groups. The column labels are X SAT math scores, Y GPA, median X value and median Y value. Group one has X values of 261, 262, 327, 350 and Y values of 50, 60, 62, and 65. The median X value is 294.5 and the median Y value is 61. Group 2 has X values of 363, 364 and 373 and Y values of 67, 70 and 71. The median X value is 364 and the median Y value is 70. Group 3 has X values of 544, 587, 624 and 741 and Y values of 86, 87, 90 and 98. The median X value is 605.5 and the median Y value is 88.5">
