<para id="fs-id1170308332499">The ordered pairs are (294.5, 61), (364, 70), and (605.5, 88.5).</para>
<para id="fs-id1170308332502">The slope can be calculated using the formula <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
     <m:mi>y</m:mi>
     <m:mn>3</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
    <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:msub>
     <m:mi>y</m:mi>
     <m:mn>1</m:mn>
    </m:msub>

   </m:mrow>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:msub>
     <m:mi>x</m:mi>
     <m:mn>3</m:mn>
    </m:msub>
    <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:msub>
     <m:mi>x</m:mi>
     <m:mn>1</m:mn>
    </m:msub>

   </m:mrow>
  </m:mfrac>
  <m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math> Substituting the median <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis> and <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> values, from the first and third groups gives <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mn>88.5</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>61</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mn>605.5</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>294.5</m:mn>
   </m:mrow>
  </m:mfrac>
<m:mtext>,</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math> which simplifies to <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mo>≈</m:mo><m:mn>0.09</m:mn>
<m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1170308376805">The y-intercept may be found using the formula <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mstyle displaystyle="true">
     <m:mo>∑</m:mo> <m:mrow>
      <m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mstyle displaystyle="true">
       <m:mo>∑</m:mo> <m:mi>x</m:mi>
      </m:mstyle>
     </m:mrow>
    </m:mstyle>
   </m:mrow>
   <m:mn>3</m:mn>
  </m:mfrac>
  <m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math> The sum of the median <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis> values is 1264, and the sum of the median <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> values is 219.5. Substituting these sums and the slope into the formula gives <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
   <m:mrow>
    <m:mn>219.5</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>0.09</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mn>1264</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
   </m:mrow>
   <m:mn>3</m:mn>
  </m:mfrac>
  <m:mtext>,</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math> which simplifies to <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>≈</m:mo><m:mn>35.25</m:mn>
<m:mtext>.</m:mtext>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1170308317633">The line of best fit is represented as <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>m</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mi>b</m:mi>
 </m:mrow>
</m:math>. Thus, the equation can be written as <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>0.09</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>35.25</m:mn>
 <m:mtext>.</m:mtext></m:mrow>
</m:math></para>
</solution>
