    <term>coefficient of correlation</term>
    <meaning id="id1167925021109">a measure developed by Karl Pearson during the early 1900s that gives the strength of association between the independent variable and the dependent variable;
<equation class="unnumbered" id="fs-id1170309748850"><label/><m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
