where <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> is the number of data points
<newline/>The coefficient cannot be more than 1 and less than –1. The closer the coefficient is to ±1, the stronger the evidence of a significant linear relationship between <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis> and <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>.
